    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-01-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-01-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="454"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d454">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Willis</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 33.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Honolulu, Hawaiian Islands</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-01-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 20, 1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your telegram of January 12, 1894, sent to W. A. Cooper, U. S. dispatch agent at
                    San Francisco, and by him forwarded, which reached here to-day.</p>
                <p>Permit me to express my thanks for your words of approval.</p>
                <p>I will, as directed, endeavor to keep the Department fully informed of the course
                    of events and will, until further notice, consider that my <pb facs="1231"
                        n="1225" xml:id="pg_1225"/> special instructions have been fully complied
                    with, the Hawaiian question being, as you now inform me, submitted to the
                    Congress.</p>
                <p>I have further to acknowledge the receipt of your dispatch No. 6 of December 23,
                    1893, in regard to Department cipher, and your dispatch No. 7 of December 30,
                    1893, inclosing copies of documents in relation to Hawaiian affairs.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Albert S. Willis.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
